summary:
The Security Council,
Recalling previous resolutions and statements on Sierra Leone, 
Affirming commitment to respect Sierra Leone's sovereignty, 
Welcoming end of conflict, progress in peace process and security improvements,
Emphasizing Government's efforts to extend authority, 
Welcoming progress in breaking link between illicit diamonds and conflict,
Concerned about illicit diamond trade, 
Determining situation in region continues to threaten international peace, 
Acting under Chapter VII,

1. Welcomes Government of Sierra Leone's report on Certificate of Origin Scheme;
2. Extends measures imposed by resolution 1306 (2000) for six months, 
   exempting rough diamonds controlled by Government under Certificate of Origin;
3. Decides measures shall terminate if Council deems it appropriate;
4. Requests Committee to continue consideration of measures;
5. Requests Secretary-General to publicize provisions;
6. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
